<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="16.[189,368,932,958]" box="[189,368,932,958]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,368,932,958]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,368,932,958]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Male genitalia</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[189,1399,978,1287]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Dark red (
<figureCitation box="[308,444,978,1005]" captionStart="Figs 13–18" captionStartId="10.[189,241,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,525,1897]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[189,1398,525,1901]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 13–18. Male genitalia. — 13–14. Belbina bergrothi. 13. Lateral view. 14. Dorsal view. — 15–16. B. bloetei. 15. Lateral view. 16. Dorsal view. — 17–18. B. bourgoini sp. nov. 17. Lateral view. 18. Dorsal view. — An = anal tube, Py = pygofer, G = gonostylus. Photographs by Y. Laurent &amp; I. Bachy." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3838829" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3838829/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Figs 15–16</figureCitation>
); pygofer higher than long and with posterior margin concave in middle in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[261,347,1014,1041]" captionStart="Figs 13–18" captionStartId="10.[189,241,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,525,1897]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[189,1398,525,1901]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 13–18. Male genitalia. — 13–14. Belbina bergrothi. 13. Lateral view. 14. Dorsal view. — 15–16. B. bloetei. 15. Lateral view. 16. Dorsal view. — 17–18. B. bourgoini sp. nov. 17. Lateral view. 18. Dorsal view. — An = anal tube, Py = pygofer, G = gonostylus. Photographs by Y. Laurent &amp; I. Bachy." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3838829" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3838829/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
); anal tube slightly elongate, 1.16 times longer than broad at apex and with lateral margins bisinuate in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[501,591,1049,1076]" captionStart="Figs 13–18" captionStartId="10.[189,241,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,525,1897]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[189,1398,525,1901]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 13–18. Male genitalia. — 13–14. Belbina bergrothi. 13. Lateral view. 14. Dorsal view. — 15–16. B. bloetei. 15. Lateral view. 16. Dorsal view. — 17–18. B. bourgoini sp. nov. 17. Lateral view. 18. Dorsal view. — An = anal tube, Py = pygofer, G = gonostylus. Photographs by Y. Laurent &amp; I. Bachy." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3838829" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3838829/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
); margin of anal opening pointed posteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[1160,1249,1049,1076]" captionStart="Figs 13–18" captionStartId="10.[189,241,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,525,1897]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[189,1398,525,1901]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 13–18. Male genitalia. — 13–14. Belbina bergrothi. 13. Lateral view. 14. Dorsal view. — 15–16. B. bloetei. 15. Lateral view. 16. Dorsal view. — 17–18. B. bourgoini sp. nov. 17. Lateral view. 18. Dorsal view. — An = anal tube, Py = pygofer, G = gonostylus. Photographs by Y. Laurent &amp; I. Bachy." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3838829" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3838829/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
) and hiding lateral margin apically in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[644,732,1084,1111]" captionStart="Figs 13–18" captionStartId="10.[189,241,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,525,1897]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[189,1398,525,1901]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 13–18. Male genitalia. — 13–14. Belbina bergrothi. 13. Lateral view. 14. Dorsal view. — 15–16. B. bloetei. 15. Lateral view. 16. Dorsal view. — 17–18. B. bourgoini sp. nov. 17. Lateral view. 18. Dorsal view. — An = anal tube, Py = pygofer, G = gonostylus. Photographs by Y. Laurent &amp; I. Bachy." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3838829" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3838829/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
); gonostyli elongate, 1.18 times longer than high (dorsal process included), strongly surpassing apex of anal tube and acutely rounded at apex in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[198,284,1154,1181]" captionStart="Figs 13–18" captionStartId="10.[189,241,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,525,1897]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[189,1398,525,1901]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 13–18. Male genitalia. — 13–14. Belbina bergrothi. 13. Lateral view. 14. Dorsal view. — 15–16. B. bloetei. 15. Lateral view. 16. Dorsal view. — 17–18. B. bourgoini sp. nov. 17. Lateral view. 18. Dorsal view. — An = anal tube, Py = pygofer, G = gonostylus. Photographs by Y. Laurent &amp; I. Bachy." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3838829" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3838829/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
); ventral margin straight on basal 1/5, then strongly excavate (
<figureCitation box="[1002,1088,1154,1181]" captionStart="Figs 13–18" captionStartId="10.[189,241,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,525,1897]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[189,1398,525,1901]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 13–18. Male genitalia. — 13–14. Belbina bergrothi. 13. Lateral view. 14. Dorsal view. — 15–16. B. bloetei. 15. Lateral view. 16. Dorsal view. — 17–18. B. bourgoini sp. nov. 17. Lateral view. 18. Dorsal view. — An = anal tube, Py = pygofer, G = gonostylus. Photographs by Y. Laurent &amp; I. Bachy." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3838829" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3838829/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
); dorsal margin with basal strong digitiform process projecting laterodorsally, strong hook laterally at middle of process projecting posteroventrally and posterior margin of process excavate between apex and hook (
<figureCitation box="[1194,1284,1225,1252]" captionStart="Figs 13–18" captionStartId="10.[189,241,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,525,1897]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[189,1398,525,1901]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 13–18. Male genitalia. — 13–14. Belbina bergrothi. 13. Lateral view. 14. Dorsal view. — 15–16. B. bloetei. 15. Lateral view. 16. Dorsal view. — 17–18. B. bourgoini sp. nov. 17. Lateral view. 18. Dorsal view. — An = anal tube, Py = pygofer, G = gonostylus. Photographs by Y. Laurent &amp; I. Bachy." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3838829" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3838829/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
); apex of digitiform process rounded and broad in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[820,908,1260,1287]" captionStart="Figs 13–18" captionStartId="10.[189,241,1928,1954]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,525,1897]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[189,1398,525,1901]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figs 13–18. Male genitalia. — 13–14. Belbina bergrothi. 13. Lateral view. 14. Dorsal view. — 15–16. B. bloetei. 15. Lateral view. 16. Dorsal view. — 17–18. B. bourgoini sp. nov. 17. Lateral view. 18. Dorsal view. — An = anal tube, Py = pygofer, G = gonostylus. Photographs by Y. Laurent &amp; I. Bachy." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3838829" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3838829/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[189,303,1326,1352]" box="[189,303,1326,1352]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,1326,1352]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,1326,1352]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[189,1399,1372,1575]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lallemand" authorityYear="1959" box="[189,371,1372,1398]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Belbina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bloetei">
<emphasis box="[189,371,1372,1398]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Belbina bloetei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a member of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1863" box="[623,698,1372,1398]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Belbina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="falleni">
<emphasis box="[623,698,1372,1398]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">falleni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
+ group, showing strong basodorsal digitiform process on gonostyli. It can be separated (1) from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1863" box="[639,746,1407,1433]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Belbina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="falleni">
<emphasis box="[639,746,1407,1433]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">B. falleni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Constant, 2014" authorityName="Constant" authorityYear="2014" box="[760,888,1407,1433]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Belbina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laetitiae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[760,888,1407,1433]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">B. laetitiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[894,987,1408,1434]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lall, V. Lallemand" authorityYear="1922" box="[998,1158,1407,1433]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Belbina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lambertoni">
<emphasis box="[998,1158,1407,1433]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">B. lambertoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lallemand, V. Lallemand" authorityYear="1922" box="[1213,1362,1408,1433]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Belbina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pionneaui">
<emphasis box="[1213,1362,1408,1433]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">B. pionneaui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the more strongly concave ventral margin of the gonostyli in lateral view; (2) from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1863" box="[1161,1268,1443,1469]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Belbina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="falleni">
<emphasis box="[1161,1268,1443,1469]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">B. falleni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the less excavate dorsal margin of the gonostyli in dorsal view; (3) from 
<taxonomicName authority="Constant, 2014" authorityName="Constant" authorityYear="2014" box="[954,1083,1478,1504]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Belbina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laetitiae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[954,1083,1478,1504]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">B. laetitiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1090,1181,1478,1504]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lall, V. Lallemand" authorityYear="1922" box="[1237,1399,1478,1504]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Belbina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lambertoni">
<emphasis box="[1237,1399,1478,1504]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">B. lambertoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the more acute apex of the gonostyli in lateral view; (4) from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lallemand, V. Lallemand" authorityYear="1922" box="[939,1088,1514,1539]" class="Insecta" family="Fulgoridae" genus="Belbina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pionneaui">
<emphasis box="[939,1088,1514,1539]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">B. pionneaui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the more rounded apex of the basodorsal digitiform process of the gonostyli.
</paragraph>
